{"entity":{"id":"rec0jwZa5ky7jSTpc","type":"chapter","slug":"rec0jwZa5ky7jSTpc","label":"Ps.137","rawId":"rec0jwZa5ky7jSTpc","book":{"id":"recKXZXO6cJwk2SxO","type":"book","slug":"ps","label":"Psalms","subtitle":"Poetry-Wisdom","count":2461,"description":"150 chapters, 1026 people, 118 places"}},"stats":{"verses":9,"people":2,"places":3,"events":0},"nodes":[{"id":"rec0jwZa5ky7jSTpc","type":"chapter","group":"focus","label":"Ps.137","slug":"ps_137","score":9},{"id":"recKXZXO6cJwk2SxO","type":"book","group":"book","label":"Psalms","slug":"ps","score":2461},{"id":"reccZB8SVU5bEMcgo","type":"person","group":"mentioned","label":"God","slug":"god_1324","score":2},{"id":"recUQWSZuOecG4z1Q","type":"person","group":"mentioned","label":"Esau (Edom)","slug":"esau_1216","score":1},{"id":"recL1WV82pXaRBQ59","type":"place","group":"mentioned","label":"Jerusalem","slug":"jerusalem_636","score":3},{"id":"recpqKANUDcRgN4HU","type":"place","group":"mentioned","label":"Babylon","slug":"babylon_151","score":2},{"id":"reczPjeq0UdahiRrn","type":"place","group":"mentioned","label":"Zion","slug":"zion_1263","score":2}],"links":[{"source":"rec0jwZa5ky7jSTpc","target":"recKXZXO6cJwk2SxO","label":"part of"},{"source":"rec0jwZa5ky7jSTpc","target":"reccZB8SVU5bEMcgo","label":"mentions"},{"source":"rec0jwZa5ky7jSTpc","target":"recUQWSZuOecG4z1Q","label":"mentions"},{"source":"rec0jwZa5ky7jSTpc","target":"recL1WV82pXaRBQ59","label":"mentions"},{"source":"rec0jwZa5ky7jSTpc","target":"recpqKANUDcRgN4HU","label":"mentions"},{"source":"rec0jwZa5ky7jSTpc","target":"reczPjeq0UdahiRrn","label":"mentions"}],"verses":[{"id":"recVYxh59OKLNtsmg","ref":"Ps.137.1","text":"By the rivers of Babylon, there we sat down, yea, we wept, when we remembered Zion.","year":-541},{"id":"recD5CM6BnVdW1OiV","ref":"Ps.137.2","text":"We hanged our harps upon the willows in the midst thereof.","year":-541},{"id":"recRmkWUqCI1XKVAh","ref":"Ps.137.3","text":"For there they that carried us away captive required of us a song; and they that wasted us required of us mirth, saying, Sing us one of the songs of Zion.","year":-541},{"id":"recXxR2dFgK1ci1MX","ref":"Ps.137.4","text":"How shall we sing the LORD’S song in a strange land?","year":-541},{"id":"recDIFjewS9kq6Mgr","ref":"Ps.137.5","text":"If I forget thee, O Jerusalem, let my right hand forget her cunning.","year":-541},{"id":"recWNrHk5qcmqgEyC","ref":"Ps.137.6","text":"If I do not remember thee, let my tongue cleave to the roof of my mouth; if I prefer not Jerusalem above my chief joy.","year":-541},{"id":"receJk7MbDXfS01VU","ref":"Ps.137.7","text":"Remember, O LORD, the children of Edom in the day of Jerusalem; who said, Rase it, rase it, even to the foundation thereof.","year":-541},{"id":"recKcfUPu3XMjsjFH","ref":"Ps.137.8","text":"O daughter of Babylon, who art to be destroyed; happy shall he be, that rewardeth thee as thou hast served us.","year":-541}]}
